raw_data.title: Help Desk Support Specialist
raw_data.description: Has overall responsibility for help desk operations associated with the identification, prioritization, and resolution of reported problems. Ensures that all phases of help desk support are properly coordinated, monitored, logged, tracked, and resolved appropriately. May maintain responsibility for maintenance and integrity of help desk software.

raw_data.title: Technical Writer
raw_data.description: Writes technical documents such as technical procedure manuals, user manuals, programming manuals, service manuals, operational specifications, and related technical publications to communicate clearly and effectively technical specifications and instructions to a wide range of audiences. Acquires subject knowledge by interviewing product developers, observing performance of production methods, referring to technical specifications, blueprints, engineering illustrations, and trade journals.

raw_data.title: Training Consultant
raw_data.description: Design and develop curriculum and associated training materials for IT systems, and software applications.  Conduct training and development programs to improve individual and organizational performance.

raw_data.title: Data Entry Operator
raw_data.description: Enters data into pre-defined input screens and databases. Relies on instructions and pre-established guidelines to perform the functions of the job.

raw_data.title: Test Engineer
raw_data.description: Responsible for conducting tests of software products and extensions to ensure that software runs smoothly and meets client needs. Has an eye for detail and is extremely comfortable working in client-facing roles. Test Engineer is part of our software development team, which extends and adapts our standard software to fit the customer requirements and needs. Works in cross-functional teams with other software engineers, systems engineers, architects, testers, and project managers that will jointly plan, implement and test our systems and solutions in the customer’s organization.

raw_data.title: Data Analyst
raw_data.description: Analyze, validate, and verify data sets and solutions to address business requirements. Consult development staff and business stakeholders on data architectures, data sets and data platforms. Coordinate the data administration technical function for data warehouse, data mart, and business intelligence development and maintenance. Monitor databases to ensure accurate and appropriate use of data and responsible for quality control of the database activities.  Plan the technical transitions between development, testing, and production phases of the workplace.  Develop appropriate programs and systems documentation. Assists with metadata repository management.  Prepare and implement data verification and testing methods for data warehouses.

raw_data.title: Data Scientist
raw_data.description: Serve as data subject matter expert (SME) when designing, developing or optimizing data driven solutions and applications.  Data mining;  extending organization's data with third party sources of information  when required; enhancing data collection procedures to include information  that is relevant for building analytic systems; processing, cleansing, and verifying the integrity of data used for analysis; conducting ad-hoc analysis and presenting results in a clear manner; creating automated anomaly detection systems and constant tracking of its performance.

raw_data.title: Database Administrator
raw_data.description: Administer and maintain databases; Serve as technical interface for database services, providing Tier III support; Support software development projects. Ensure databases and site collections databases are configured in compliance with policies, configuration standards and governance. Maintain databases for data presentation solutions leveraging SharePoint, Reporting Services and other similar platforms.

raw_data.title: System Administrator
raw_data.description: Maintain smooth operation of multi-user computer systems, including coordination with network engineers. Monitor and manage system resources, including CPU usage, disk usage, and response times to maintain operating efficiency.  Perform systems security administration functions, including creating user profiles and accounts. Other duties may include setting up administrator accounts, maintain system documentation, tune system performance, install system-wide software and allocate mass storage space. Interact with users and evaluate vendor products.

raw_data.title: Web Developer
raw_data.description: Develop custom programs for web sites.  Create web applications and components from the requirements stage, through design and production deployment. Possess a thorough knowledge of programming and server software operations. Develop new web applications through packaged and customized applications. Creates web front-end user interface to new or existing databases using a combination of HTML, CSS, JavaScript, SQL, C#, Python, AngularJS or other languages, to make business applications accessible. Design and implement user-driven templates, databases and interfaces for ease of use.

raw_data.title: Computer Graphics Specialist
raw_data.description: Provides computer graphics design and development support to projects and designs user interface screens. Work is performed using graphic design software, user interface layout, publishing software, and other tools. Items produced include software users’ manuals, software user interfaces and icons.

raw_data.title: UI/UX Designer
raw_data.description: UI/UX designers builds bridges among businesses and customers by providing solutions that are intuitively developed for a targeted audience. UI/UX Designers tasks involve:  provide wireframes, information architecture, user experience, and user interface designs for software, web, and mobile applications. Incorporate client, design team’s feedback, and ensure that the designs will lead to software, which fulfills the specs set by the Product/Project Managers. They will validate business assumptions by testing those wireframes with potential customers and prepare design assets and specs for a right implementation.  UI/UX Designers work in Illustrator, Photoshop, Sketch App, Figma, and Invision with superb knowledge of software, web, and mobile design processes.

raw_data.title: Software Developer
raw_data.description: Provide expertise and direction in the development and/or modification of computer-based scientific, technical, and business software systems. Leverage expertise to design develop, code, test, and debug software.  May work in one or several areas, such as equipment or software design, engineering evaluation or test, statistical analysis and modeling.

raw_data.title: Software Engineer
raw_data.description: The Software Engineer assists our clients and business partners with implementing our software solutions, in their technical infrastructure and according to their working procedures. The Software Engineer is a technical “problem-solver” and extremely comfortable working in client-facing roles. The Software Engineer is part of our software development team, which extends and adapts our standard software to fit the customer requirements and needs, and works in cross-functional teams with other software engineers, systems engineers, architects, testers, and project managers that will jointly plan and implement our systems and solutions in the customer’s organization.

raw_data.title: DevOps Engineer
raw_data.description: A DevOps Engineer combines an understanding of both engineering and coding. A DevOps Engineer works with various departments to create and develop systems within a company. From creating and implementing systems software to analyzing data to improve existing ones, a DevOps Engineer increases productivity in the workplace. A DevOps Engineer works to balance various aspects of a project, most of them complex issues such as programming and network building.

raw_data.title: DevSecOps Engineer
raw_data.description: Provide technical expertise within cloud and virtualization-based development, test, evaluation, and production environments. Prepare required documentation, including both program-level and user level documentation. Perform security maintenance of pipeline systems and applications.

raw_data.title: Solution Architect
raw_data.description: The Solution Architect is responsible for projects and proposals with the expectation of adopting innovative best practices for IT delivery. Understands our customers’ business and technical needs to best design solutions and the ability to push technical boundaries. Engages with the subject matter experts, product architects, engineers, and international standards community. Defines the architecture runway to support this domain for product and services launch. Provides technical and solution leadership in delivering architectural artifacts that promote reusability, modularity and scalability across the various lines of products. Leads and facilitates meetings and discussions to elicit business, product requirements to define and deliver architectural solutions and prescriptive guidance. Drives end-to-end process and solution leadership to successfully complete integration & implementation. Articulates the problem statement and openly bring up challenges, roadblocks and impediments, negotiate, influence and drive solutions with military leaders and industry partners.

raw_data.title: Business Analyst
raw_data.description: Conduct interviews with customers to gather the requirements. Create functional specifications and coordinate with design and development teams. Develop business solutions for clients to include defining, analyzing and documenting requirements. Develop, monitor, and maintain metrics.  Perform risk management.

raw_data.title: Project Manager
raw_data.description: Leads team towards success. Provides direction and makes team understand what is expected of them. Clearly explains the roles of each member of the team. The project manager is a link between clients, the team and supervisors. Coordinates and transfers all the relevant information from the clients to the team and reports to the upper management. Works closely with analysts, software designers and other staff members and communicate the goals of the project. Monitors the progress of the project, taking action accordingly. Guides team at every step and ensures that the team has cohesion. Provides advice to the team wherever they need it and points them in the right direction.

raw_data.title: Agile Consultant
raw_data.description: Consults clients on the strategic implementation of the concepts of Agile software development methodologies such as Agile Scrum.   Consultation includes methods for team development, communications, customer collaboration, user stories development, stakeholder engagement, product backlog management, sprint cycle planning and execution, change management, task board/Kanban techniques, and coaching.

raw_data.title: Product Owner
raw_data.description: Product Owner is a professional responsible for setting, prioritizing, and accepting the work generated by a team in order to ensure the most valuable and proper functionality of the product. Additional responsibilities including backlog grooming, managing backlog based on the feature requests and schedule releases.

raw_data.title: Scrum Master
raw_data.description: A scrum master helps oversee the scrum and development team. They are knowledgeable in Agile methodology and scrum and able to educate others. They also act as a buffer between the scrum team and product owner and maintain a safe working environment for the team by helping with conflict resolution.

raw_data.title: Proposal writing specialist
raw_data.description: Analyses the Government solicitations or Commercial opportunities and create proposals responses. Coordinates with Opportunity, Vendor, Customer, Approval Management teams to finalize the proposals before submission.  Expertise in Microsoft office suite to organize and format the proposal based on the opportunity requirements.
